doc.after: Gorgosaurus libratus was first described by Lawrence Lambe in 1914 19 20 Its name is derived from the Greek gorgos fierce or terrible and saurus lizard 21 The type species is G libratus the specific epithet balanced is the past participle of the Latin verb librare meaning to balance 20
